{"name": "odoo-addon-dms-field", "metadata": {"name": "odoo-addon-dms-field", "version": "16.0.1.1.2.2", "classifiers": ["Framework :: Odoo", "Framework :: Odoo :: 16.0", "License :: OSI Approved :: GNU Lesser General Public License v3 (LGPLv3)", "Programming Language :: Python"], "home_page": "https://github.com/OCA/dms", "license": "LGPL-3", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["odoo-addon-dms", "odoo"], "summary": "Create DMS View and allow to use them inside a record", "upload_time": 1732675589}, "documentation": ["---\nsubstitutions:\n  badge1: |-\n    ```{image} https://img.shields.io/badge/maturity-Beta-yellow.png\n    :alt: Beta\n    :target: https://odoo-community.org/page/development-status\n    ```\n  badge2: |-\n    ```{image} https://img.shields.io/badge/licence-LGPL--3-blue.png\n    :alt: 'License: LGPL-3'\n    :target: http://www.gnu.org/licenses/lgpl-3.0-standalone.html\n    ```\n  badge3: |-\n    ```{image} https://img.shields.io/badge/github-OCA%2Fdms-lightgray.png?logo=github\n    :alt: OCA/dms\n    :target: https://github.com/OCA/dms/tree/16.0/dms_field\n    ```\n  badge4: |-\n    ```{image} https://img.shields.io/badge/weblate-Translate%20me-F47D42.png\n    :alt: Translate me on Weblate\n    :target: https://translation.odoo-community.org/projects/dms-16-0/dms-16-0-dms_field\n    ```\n  badge5: |-\n    ```{image} https://img.shields.io/badge/runboat-Try%20me-875A7B.png\n    :alt: Try me on Runboat\n    :target: https://runboat.odoo-community.org/builds?repo=OCA/dms&target_branch=16.0\n    ```\n---\n\n# DMS Field\n\n% !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!\n% !! This file is generated by oca-gen-addon-readme !!\n% !! changes will be overwritten.                   !!\n% !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!\n% !! source digest: sha256:8241858f48437db5c6c964e34336698c62b272ec1baf327974dd5987da9e11ee\n% !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!\n\n{{ badge1 }} {{ badge2 }} {{ badge3 }} {{ badge4 }} {{ badge5 }}\n\nThis addon creates a new kind of view and allows to define a folder\nrelated to a record.\n\n**Table of contents**\n\n```{contents}\n:local: true\n```\n\n## Configuration\n\nTo use the embedded view in any module, the module must inherit from the mixin\ndms.field.mixin (You have an example with res.partner in this module).\n\nOnce this is done, in the form view of the model we will have to add the following:\n\n```xml\n<field name=\"dms_directory_ids\" mode=\"dms_list\" />\n```\n\nIn addition, it will be necessary to create an Embedded DMS template for this model.\n\n1. *Go to Documents > Configuration > Embedded DMS templates* and create a new record.\n2. Set a storage, a model (res.partner for example) and the access groups you want.\n3. You can also use expressions in \"Directory format name\", for example: {{object.name}}\n4. Click on the \"Documents\" tab icon and a folder hierarchy will be created.\n5. You can set here the hierarchy of directories, subdirectories and files you need, this hierarchy will be used as a base when creating a new record (res.partner for example).\n\n## Usage\n\n#. Go to the form view of an existing partner and click on the \"DMS\" tab icon, a hierarchy of\nfolders and files linked to that record will be created.\n#. Create a new partner. A hierarchy of folders and files linked to that record will be created.\n\n## Known issues / Roadmap\n\n- Add drag & drop compatibility to the dms_tree mode\n- Multiple selection support (e.g. cut several files and paste to another folder).\n\n## Bug Tracker\n\nBugs are tracked on [GitHub Issues](https://github.com/OCA/dms/issues).\nIn case of trouble, please check there if your issue has already been reported.\nIf you spotted it first, help us to smash it by providing a detailed and welcomed\n[feedback](https://github.com/OCA/dms/issues/new?body=module:%20dms_field%0Aversion:%2016.0%0A%0A**Steps%20to%20reproduce**%0A-%20...%0A%0A**Current%20behavior**%0A%0A**Expected%20behavior**).\n\nDo not contact contributors directly about support or help with technical issues.\n\n## Credits\n\n### Authors\n\n- Creu Blanca\n\n### Contributors\n\n- Enric Tobella \\<<mailto:etobella@creublanca.es>>\n\n- Jaime Arroyo \\<<mailto:jaime.arroyo@creublanca.es>>\n\n- [Tecnativa](https://www.tecnativa.com):\n\n  - V\u00edctor Mart\u00ednez\n  - Carlos Roca\n\n### Maintainers\n\nThis module is maintained by the OCA.\n\n```{image} https://odoo-community.org/logo.png\n:alt: Odoo Community Association\n:target: https://odoo-community.org\n```\n\nOCA, or the Odoo Community Association, is a nonprofit organization whose\nmission is to support the collaborative development of Odoo features and\npromote its widespread use.\n\nThis module is part of the [OCA/dms](https://github.com/OCA/dms/tree/16.0/dms_field) project on GitHub.\n\nYou are welcome to contribute. To learn how please visit <https://odoo-community.org/page/Contribute>.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "odoo.addons.dms_field.models.dms_field_mixin", "documentation": ["Copyright 2020 Creu Blanca", "Copyright 2024 Tecnativa - V\u00edctor Mart\u00ednez", "License LGPL-3.0 or later (http://www.gnu.org/licenses/lgpl)."], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "odoo.addons.dms_field.models.dms_field_mixin.DMSFieldMixin", "bases": ["models.AbstractModel"], "methods": [{"name": "odoo.addons.dms_field.models.dms_field_mixin.DMSFieldMixin.models_to_track_dms_field_template", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Models to be tracked for dms field templates\n:args:\n:returns: list of models"]}, {"name": "odoo.addons.dms_field.models.dms_field_mixin.DMSFieldMixin.create", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "vals_list", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Create a dms directory when creating the record if exist a template."]}, {"name": "odoo.addons.dms_field.models.dms_field_mixin.DMSFieldMixin.write", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "vals", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["When modifying a record that has linked directories and changing the\nuser_id field it is necessary to update the auto-generated access group\n(name and explicit_user_ids)."]}, {"name": "odoo.addons.dms_field.models.dms_field_mixin.DMSFieldMixin.unlink", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["When deleting a record, we also delete the linked directories and the\nauto-generated access group."]}], "class_variables": [{"name": "odoo.addons.dms_field.models.dms_field_mixin.DMSFieldMixin._name", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "odoo.addons.dms_field.models.dms_field_mixin.DMSFieldMixin._description", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "odoo.addons.dms_field.models.dms_field_mixin.DMSFieldMixin.dms_directory_ids", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "odoo.addons.dms_field.models.dms_storage", "documentation": ["Copyright 2020 Creu Blanca", "Copyright 2024 Tecnativa - V\u00edctor Mart\u00ednez", "License LGPL-3.0 or later (http://www.gnu.org/licenses/lgpl)."], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "odoo.addons.dms_field.models.dms_storage.DmsStorage", "bases": ["models.Model"], "methods": [{"name": "odoo.addons.dms_field.models.dms_storage.DmsStorage._build_documents_storage", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "storage", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "odoo.addons.dms_field.models.dms_storage.DmsStorage.get_js_tree_data", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation":